Interface JCSMPResponseListener


  • public interface JCSMPResponseListener
    A callback interface to handle responses from asynchronous subscription operations.

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      • handleError

        void handleError(Object key,
                 Exception cause)
        This method is invoked whenever a subscription operation fails.

        Error responses from the appliance

        If an error response is available, it is represented as a JCSMPErrorResponseException. The following subcodes can be present to provide further information about why the subscription operation was rejected:
        • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.SUBSCRIPTION_INVALID
        • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.SUBSCRIPTION_ALREADY_PRESENT
        • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.SUBSCRIPTION_TOO_MANY
        • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.OUT_OF_RESOURCES
        • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.SUBSCRIPTION_ACL_DENIED
        Parameters:
        key - The correlation key of the subscription operation with which the error condition is associated.
        cause - The error condition.
